-- SEC Awards $1 Million for Information Provided in Pequot Case
-- Gregory Mott
-- 2010-07-23T19:13:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/sec-pays-1-million-for-information-given-in-pequot-insider-trading-case.html

          
          
             The U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission said it will pay $1 million to two people who
provided information and documents leading to civil penalties in
the Pequot Capital Management Inc. insider-trading case.  
 The SEC’s award to Glen Kaiser and Karen Kaiser of
Southbury, Connecticut, was announced today in a statement on
the agency’s website. The award is the largest paid by the SEC
for information provided in connection with an insider trading
case, the agency said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Gregory Mott in Washington at 
 gmott1@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
